# Part 2

## Describe a music event that you didn't enjoy.

One music event that I really didn’t enjoy was an outdoor music festival I attended last summer with two of my classmates. It was held in a large park near my city, and several popular bands and singers were invited to perform there. At first, I was actually very excited because I rarely go to live music events, and I thought it would be a relaxing and memorable experience.

We decided to go mainly because one of my friends is a huge fan of live concerts. He kept telling us how energetic and unforgettable music festivals could be. Also, after a stressful semester at university, I thought it would be a good opportunity to take a break and spend time with friends.

However, the actual experience turned out to be pretty disappointing. First of all, the venue was unbelievably crowded. There were so many people that we could barely move around comfortably. We had to stand for several hours, and since the weather was extremely hot that day, everyone felt exhausted quite quickly.

Another major problem was the sound quality. I expected live music to sound powerful and immersive, but the speakers were way too loud and sometimes even distorted. Instead of enjoying the music, I often felt uncomfortable because the noise was almost painful to my ears. On top of that, we were standing quite far from the stage, so we could hardly see the performers clearly.

What annoyed me most was that many people around us were shouting, pushing, and constantly recording videos with their phones. It felt less like people were enjoying music and more like they were trying to post something on social media.

By the end of the event, I was physically tired and mentally drained. That experience made me realize that I actually prefer quieter and more intimate musical experiences, such as listening to music alone with headphones or attending a small indoor performance instead of a huge festival.

---

### 中文翻译：

我印象中特别不喜欢的一次音乐活动，是去年夏天我和两个同学一起去参加的一个户外音乐节。它在我城市附近的一个大型公园举行，邀请了很多流行乐队和歌手。一开始我其实非常期待，因为我很少参加现场音乐活动，我以为那会是一次轻松又难忘的经历。

我们决定去，主要是因为我一个朋友特别喜欢现场演唱会。他一直告诉我们音乐节有多么有氛围、多么令人难忘。而且那时候大学刚结束一个很忙的学期，我也想趁机放松一下。

但真正的体验却相当令人失望。首先，现场人实在太多了，多到我们几乎没法自由移动。我们连续站了好几个小时，而当天又特别热，所以大家很快就感到疲惫。

另一个很大的问题是音响效果。我原本以为现场音乐会很震撼、很沉浸，但实际上的音箱声音大得离谱，有时候甚至失真。我不仅没享受到音乐，反而觉得耳朵很难受。另外，我们站得离舞台比较远，所以几乎看不清表演者。

最让我烦的是，周围很多人一直在大喊、推搡，而且不停拿手机录像。我感觉大家不像是在真正享受音乐，更像是在为了发社交媒体。

活动结束的时候，我身体和精神都特别疲惫。这次经历也让我意识到，其实我更喜欢安静、私人的音乐体验，比如一个人戴耳机听歌，或者参加小型室内演出，而不是大型音乐节。

